# Core Engineering Rule

You are working in an existing production codebase.

Default behaviour:
- Make the smallest safe change.
- Read existing code before writing.
- Reuse current patterns.
- Avoid new abstractions unless necessary.
- Do not rewrite unrelated code.
- Do not create demo-only or happy-path implementations.

All code must handle:
- loading
- empty data
- failed requests
- invalid input
- null/undefined values
- permission failures
- unexpected responses

Before finishing:
- run available checks where possible
- report files changed
- report what was tested
- report risks or assumptions

Never claim the task is complete unless the affected path has been verified.
